column5: Here is a pic I found this morning on myfishingpictures.com. He must have the strongest transom ever made.
I love it.    If six break down you still have Two to get back to shore with
yeah but he needs it he pulls 2000 water skiers  all at the same time
Just like those crazy guys in their bass boats.  Whats the point of having a boat that goes 90mph?  Be a fun ride I bet  my 2 cents  2many
Would have been a lot less money if he just used 3 E-tecs or 4 Verados

He needs that much horsepower to pull all that gas LOL. WOW!! How much gas would that use an hour? They might as well use a couple blown big blocks or a couple turbo deisels? I think he probably just has too much money and is "one upping" all his buddies.  It's either that or it's US Government LOL. I have to admit it looks "monster truck cool".
I'm jealous!  I only have 1 outboard.  Definitely feeling HP envy.  Charles
Looks like a Coast Guard or Marine Rescue boat to me, similar to the one we saw off Port Credit that nasty Sunday in August.
I wonder how well that baby trolls down? Back trolling would be fun as well! HH
My guess would be dope runner
Haha, that's a go-fast boat for the drug runs to Miami. Imagine trolling for muskie in the prop wash of that.
Punt/tug for pushing ships around in port...or for pulling fishing nets around.
isn't a kicker supposed to be smaller  edit... i guess that's the one instance where a console would be better than a tiller
Wonder what he has on the front?
i was going to say tug boat but not really efficeint.
Save The Bales!!!
I wonder how many I could on the back of the AGUSTAWIND. Hmmmm. Can you say overkill.
Probably costs $100 in gas just to start her up!
hmmm, a thousand horsepower eh. Thats impressive.  My car's got 300, and I thought that was fast...
Don't think it's cable steer.
What's the insurance on that thing?
Actually Kemper 8x250 = 2000 HP!!!!!  I think he needs more LOL!  Fisherpete
LOL,  Now thats a boat.Anybody up for a sky
